title: For Sale:  COLT Model 1903 Pistol - .32 ACP - Dated 1912
postcontent: This semi-automatic pistol designed by John Browning was produced from 1903 until 1945.  It's 3/4"wide by 7" long body and shrouded hammer made it the perfect conceal carry pistol for the likes of Al Capone, Clyde Barrow, and John Dillinger.  The 1903/1908 pistols were also a favorite of U.S. Military Generals Patton, Marshall, Bradley, and Eisenhower.  The 1903 was the first gun ever manufactured with a grip safety.  Some call it the mini-1911.  Inland Mfg. has recently began reproducing the 1903 at a current list price of $1345.The pistol I am selling was made in 1912 and is free of rust, pitting, peeling, and scratches.  The blueing has faded in some areas with a slight tinge of brown patina, not to be confused with rust.  I did clean the pistol with Barricade Protectant prior to photographing to give it a shiny look.  This is a Type III production with all components being correct and original.  The magazine is a Type I with full blueing, dual pinned base, and unmarked base plate, which was used from 1903-1913.  Not all 1903's came with the two-tone magazine as many believe.  The Fire Blue finish on the trigger and safety/slide lock is still evident and correct. Grips are are the correct second style used on Type III pistols.  Details are original right down to the circled rampant colt logo on the left rear of slide.  The barrel is clean and shiny with no rust, and the pistol functions flawlessly.These pistol is a 104 year old part of history that will make for interesting conversation among those that appreciate collectible firearms, and likely won't depreciate in value.Out of state shipment must be to a licensed FFL for an additional $35.  Cash or money order payment only, NO TRADES !  Sale must comply with all state and federal firearms purchase and shipping requirements.
